[SN]TITLE[SN]
Woman, 81, in court after driver dies in Ceredigion crash

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
An 81-year-old woman has denied causing the death of a father by dangerous driving following a crash in Ceredigion.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
David England, 67, from Llandre, Aberystwyth, died after the A4519 crash in March 2015. His daughter was also seriously injured.
Margaret Christopher, of Banks, Lancashire, also denied causing serious injury by dangerous driving at Swansea Crown Court.
She was released on bail.
